Public Domain (US Government work)

The IGRF-14 Fortran reference implementation is released by NOAA
National Centers for Environmental Information (NCEI) at:

    http://www.ngdc.noaa.gov/IAGA/vmod/igrf14.f

The IGRF coefficient set itself is a product of the International
Association of Geomagnetism and Aeronomy (IAGA) Working Group V-MOD,
distributed freely for scientific and engineering use without
royalty.

The Fortran source distributed by NOAA NCEI carries no copyright
notice; works of the United States Government are in the public
domain under 17 U.S.C. § 105.

Historical authorship of the Fortran reference:
  Susan Macmillan (BGS), August 2003 — 9th generation refactor
  Susan Macmillan (BGS), December 2004 — IGRF-10 update
  Susan Macmillan (BGS), December 2009 — IGRF-11 update
  Susan Macmillan (BGS), December 2014 — IGRF-12 update
  William Brown (BGS), December 2019 / February 2020 — IGRF-13 update
  Ciaran Beggan (BGS), November 2024 — IGRF-14 update

K26 vendors the IGRF-14 reference under the public-domain treatment
indicated by NCEI's release.
